        {
          "question_format": "mcq",
          "question": "To prove 3n^2 - 4n + 10 is positive for all values of n, what is the correct completed square form?",
          "options": [
            "3(n - 2/3)^2 + 26/3",
            "3(n + 2/3)^2 - 26/3",
            "(3n - 2)^2 + 6",
            "3(n - 4/3)^2 + 10"
          ],
          "correct_option": "A",
          "explanation": "3(n² - 4n/3) + 10 = 3[(n - 2/3)² - 4/9] + 10 = 3(n - 2/3)² - 4/3 + 10 = 3(n - 2/3)² + 26/3. This is always ≥ 26/3 > 0.",
          "diagram_required": "none"
        }
      ]
